records.addlTxt: Received and Filed: Attorney Michael Plaisted

Defendant Brittany Elizabeth Stokoe appeared by video.  Attorney Michael B Plaisted appeared as a friend of the court by video for Brittany Elizabeth Stokoe.  Attorney Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a status conference. Defense is waiting to be appointed by the State Public Defender's Office. Court adjourns matter for a status of counsel. Case remains calendared in Branch 11.
Status conference scheduled for November 9, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered Justice Point SUPERVISION.  
-No alcohol or illegal drugs unless prescribed by doctor.

Defendant Brittany Elizabeth Stokoe in court with attorney Michael B Plaisted.  Defendant Brittany Elizabeth Stokoe in custody.  Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Brittany Elizabeth Stokoe appeared by video means with Attorney.
Case in court for return on warrant.  State requested bench warrant to be withdrawn.  Court grants state's request and VACATES bench warrant.  Defense requested inital appearance and waives formal reading of complaint and preliminary hearing.  Court grants defense request.  Initial appearance proceeded.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant pled not guilty.  Court hears arguments as to bail.  For reasons as set forth on the record, court orders $1000.00 PR bond with turnover to JusticePoint.  Case scheduled for status conference.  Status conference scheduled for October 07, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Case scheduled for status conference for August 8, 2022 at 3:00 pm; both parties agreed to date, via email.  Defendant to appear by zoom.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant Brittany Elizabeth Stokoe not in court.  Stephanie Krueger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. The forfeiture order is stayed for 30 days pending notice to the defendant. Court makes a finding that there is no possible victim identified, therefore, restitution is not an issue.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 7/18/22 @ 2:30p
